===Overview===
'''Mys-Tech'''  is an [[United Kingdom|British]] multinational chemical corporation with worldwide interests. It is headquartered in [[London (England)|London]], [[UK]]. Mys-Tech employs thousands people with facilities all over the world.

===Origin===
In the year 987, A.D. seven members of a druid cult made a deal with the demon [[Mephisto (Earth-616)|Mephisto]]: in exchange for immortality, they agreed to funnel souls into [[Mephisto's Realm]].{{R|Warheads Vol 1 1}}

Over the subsequent millennium, the mages acquired great wealth and became the board members a London-based corporation named Mys-Tech. To pay their debt to Mephisto, the Mys-Tech board plotted to take over the world and kill vast numbers of innocents.{{R|Warheads Vol 1 1}}

===Modern Era===
Their assets included the Un-Earth, a model of the planet that operated like a voodoo doll, and the Warheads, mercenaries who could travel through wormholes to other dimensions or times. The board members eventually transformed themselves into beings of even greater power known as the Techno-Wizards.{{r|Warheads #1}}
